parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle assembly can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Unusual bumping noise
vehicle stops suddenly
rear axle assembly is damaged or rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission failure
vehicle stops suddenly
transmission needs to be replaced multiple times
no prior warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A crimped fuel supply line can cause fuel to leak, leading to a potential engine fire, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor
fuel dripping or spraying from the fuel supply line connection
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: Engine stalling or failure to start
difficulty starting the engine
loss of power or performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch support bar can cause the top hatch to fall, resulting in injury to people, particularly those standing nearby or attempting to access the rear cargo area.
symptoms: The rear hatch support bar fails to hold the top hatch up
the top hatch falls suddenly
people are hit in the head or injured by the falling hatch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brakes locking up under abnormal foot pressure can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The rear brakes lock up or grab suddenly
the vehicle skids or loses traction
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ABS system being active all the time and pulsing constantly can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake, leading to driver distraction and potentially affecting vehicle control.
symptoms: The ABS system is active even on dry roads
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
the vehicle shakes or vibrates when braking
the ABS warning light is illuminated.
